Wow, I'm getting sick of all of these generic "Stop leeching and seed" comments.  How retarded can these people be? A leecher is someone who is downloading the file from the seeders.  The seeders have 100% of the file.  So, basic logic tells us that a leecher can't start seeding a file that he doesn't have 100% of, can he?  The seeders have only so much bandwidth and it is spread evenly through the leechers.  This is also, more or less, a first come first serve basis.  With almost 10 times the amount of leechers than seeders, the available bandwidth is spread very thin.  Before you retards creat an account and start jumping down the leechers throats, do a little reasearch and find out what a leecher is and find out how torrents work, otherwise you just run the risk of making yourself sound even more retarded.

@azza3211
Probably the biggest reason is because movies are a fraction of the size of games.  The leechers get done downloading faster and are able to start seeding much sooner with a 700MB-1.4GB file than with 13GB.  Download speed is also reliant on the seeder's upload speed, which varies from person to person.  On this particular torrent, I was getting between 20 and 40 kb/s, but on EZ's I'm getting 1 MB, so I stopped this one.
